#. Tag: title
#: storage_raidroot.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring software RAID for the root partition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: meta
#: storage_raidroot.xml:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure software RAID for the root partition by following these requirements and steps to ensure a successful setup process is completed"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: storage_raidroot.xml:17
#, no-c-format
msgid "2022-11-04"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "In &productname;, the Device Mapper RAID tool has been integrated into the &yast; Partitioner. You can use the partitioner at install time to create a software RAID for the system device that contains your root ( <filename>/</filename> ) partition. The <filename>/boot</filename> partition cannot be stored on a RAID partition unless it is RAID&nbsp;1."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_raidroot.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/boot/efi</filename> on RAID&nbsp;1 might not boot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "When creating the <filename>/boot/efi</filename> partition on RAID, keep in mind that in some cases the firmware might not recognize the boot partition on RAID. The firmware then refuses to boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_raidroot.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Prerequisites for using a software RAID device for the root partition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ensure that your configuration meets the following requirements:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "You need two hard disks to create the RAID&nbsp;1 mirror device. The hard disks should be similarly sized. The RAID assumes the size of the smaller drive. The block storage devices can be any combination of local (in or directly attached to the machine), Fibre Channel storage subsystems, or iSCSI storage subsystems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "A separate partition for <filename>/boot</filename> is not required if you install the boot loader in the MBR. If installing the boot loader in the MBR is not an option, <filename>/boot</filename> needs to reside on a separate partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "For UEFI machines, you need to set up a dedicated <filename>/boot/efi</filename> partition. It needs to be VFAT-formatted, and may reside on the RAID 1 device to prevent booting problems in case the physical disk with <filename>/boot/efi</filename> fails."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are using hardware RAID devices, do not attempt to run software RAIDs on top of it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are using iSCSI target devices, you need to enable the iSCSI initiator support before you create the RAID device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "If your storage subsystem provides multiple I/O paths between the server and its directly attached local devices, Fibre Channel devices, or iSCSI devices that you want to use in the software RAID, you need to enable the multipath support before you create the RAID device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: storage_raidroot.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting up the system with a software RAID device for the root ( <filename>/</filename> ) partition"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the installation with &yast; and proceed as described in <xref linkend=\"cha-install\"/> until you reach the <guimenu>Suggested Partitioning</guimenu> step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Expert Partitioner</guimenu> to open the custom partitioning tool. You can use the suggested proposal, or you can use the existing proposal."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "(Optional) If there are iSCSI target devices that you want to use, you need to enable the iSCSI Initiator software by choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>Configure</guimenu> <guimenu>Configure iSCSI</guimenu> </menuchoice> from the upper-left section of the screen. Refer to <xref linkend=\"cha-iscsi\"/> for further details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "(Optional) If there are FCoE target devices that you want to use, you need to configure the interface by clicking <menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>Configure</guimenu> <guimenu>Configure FCoE</guimenu> </menuchoice> from the upper left section of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:133
#, no-c-format
msgid "(Optional) If you need to discard the partitioning changes, click <menuchoice><guimenu>System</guimenu><guimenu>Rescan Devices</guimenu></menuchoice> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set up the <guimenu>Linux RAID</guimenu> format for each of the devices you want to use for the software RAID. You should use RAID for <filename>/</filename> , <filename>/boot/efi</filename> , or swap partitions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the left panel, select <guimenu>Hard Disks</guimenu> and select the device you want to use, then click <guimenu>Add Partition</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Under <guimenu>New Partition Size</guimenu> , specify the size to use, then click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Under <guimenu>Role</guimenu> , choose <guimenu>Raw Volume (unformatted)</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <guimenu>Do not format</guimenu> and <guimenu>Do not mount</guimenu> and set the <guimenu>Partition ID</guimenu> to <guimenu>Linux RAID</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> and repeat these instructions for the second partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create the RAID device for the <filename>/</filename> partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the left panel, select <guimenu>RAID</guimenu> and then <guimenu>Add RAID</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:292
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the desired <guimenu>RAID Type</guimenu> for the <filename>/</filename> partition and the <guimenu>RAID name</guimenu> to <literal>system</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the two RAID devices you prepared in the previous step from the <guimenu>Available Devices</guimenu> section and <guimenu>Add</guimenu> them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the chunk size from the drop-down box. Sticking with the default is a safe choice."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:325
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the left panel, click the <guimenu>RAID</guimenu> . In the <guimenu>Device Overview</guimenu> tab, select your new RAID and click <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Under <guimenu>Role</guimenu> , select <guimenu>Operating System</guimenu> and proceed with <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the <guimenu>File System</guimenu> and set the mount point to <filename>/</filename> . Leave the dialog with <filename>Next</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:384
#, no-c-format
msgid "The software RAID device is managed by Device Mapper, and creates a device under the <filename>/dev/md/system</filename> path."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:390
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optionally, you can create a swap partition in RAID. Use similar steps to those described above, but under <guimenu>Role</guimenu> , select <guimenu>swap</guimenu> . Select the file system and mount point as shown below. Click <guimenu>Next</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optionally, for UEFI machines, use similar steps to create the <filename>/boot/efi</filename> mounted partition. Remember that only RAID&nbsp;1 is supported for <filename>/boot/efi</filename> , and the partition needs to be formatted with the FAT32 file system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:424
#, no-c-format
msgid "The partitioning then looks as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:439
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Accept</guimenu> to leave the partitioner."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:442
#, no-c-format
msgid "The new proposal appears on the <guimenu>Suggested Partitioning</guimenu> page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:448
#, no-c-format
msgid "Continue with the installation. For UEFI machines with a separate <filename>/boot/efi</filename> partition, click <guimenu>Booting</guimenu> on the <guimenu>Installation Settings</guimenu> screen and set <guimenu>GRUB2 for EFI</guimenu> as the <guimenu>Boot Loader</guimenu> . Check that the <guimenu>Enable Secure Boot Support</guimenu> option is activated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: storage_raidroot.xml:456
#, no-c-format
msgid "Whenever you reboot your server, Device Mapper is started at boot time so that the software RAID is automatically recognized, and the operating system on the root ( <literal>/</literal> ) partition can be started."
msgstr ""

